{
  "answer": "**The work *Kalpabuddha* (by Unknown, work slug `unknown-kalpabuddha-d760dc`) matches this description precisely.** Each of its five chapters is dedicated to one of the Pañcatathāgatas (Five Tathāgatas), assigning them to the specified internal organs as their bodily abode (*gātra-sthāna*). Chapter 1 covers the central figure (Vairocana, as the first of the Pañcatathāgatas), Chapter 2 Akṣobhya, Chapter 3 Ratnasambhava, Chapter 4 Amitābha, and Chapter 5 Amoghasiddhi.[^1][^2][^3][^4][^5]\n\nHere are verbatim quotes of the residence formulas from Chapters 1, 2, 4, and 5 (Chapter 3 is slightly shorter but follows the same pattern):\n\n- **Chapter 1 (Vairocana)**: \"Now, as for his residence in the body, the inside of the **heart** is his abode.\"[^1]\n- **Chapter 2 (Akṣobhya)**: \"Now, as for his residence in the body, the inside of the **lungs** is his abode.\"[^2]\n- **Chapter 4 (Amitābha)**: \"Now, as for his residence in the body, the inside of the **liver** is his abode.\"[^4]\n- **Chapter 5 (Amoghasiddhi)**: \"Now, as for his residence in the body, the inside of the **gall bladder** is his abode.\"[^5]\n\n(Chapter 3, for completeness: \"The inside of the **spleen** is his abode.\"[^3])\n\n[^1]: *Kalpabuddha*, [paragraph](/works/unknown-kalpabuddha-d760dc/01/translation/#p-e1c8df).\n[^2]: *Kalpabuddha*, [paragraph](/works/unknown-kalpabuddha-d760dc/02/translation/#p-5a580a).\n[^3]: *Kalpabuddha*, [paragraph](/works/unknown-kalpabuddha-d760dc/03/translation/#p-68d96e).\n[^4]: *Kalpabuddha*, [paragraph](/works/unknown-kalpabuddha-d760dc/04/translation/#p-60c6c3).\n[^5]: *Kalpabuddha*, [paragraph](/works/unknown-kalpabuddha-d760dc/05/translation/#p-8f8def).",
